s-on-natural-causes-authorities-carry-out-health-checks-of-cheetahs%5C%22%3Esaid%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%20July%2023.%20The%20authorities%20also%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Ftwo-more-cheetahs-brought-back-to-enclosures-in-kuno%5C%22%3Ecaptured%3C%2Fa%3E%20two%20cheetahs%2C%20Prabhas%20and%20Veera%2C%20on%20Wednesday%2C%20July%2026.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThough%20efforts%20have%20been%20on%20for%20at%20least%20two%20days%20now%20to%20catch%20the%20female%20cheetahs%2C%20Nirva%20and%20Dhatri%2C%20the%20last%20free-ranging%20cheetahs%20in%20Kuno%2C%20the%20teams%20on%20the%20ground%20have%20not%20been%20able%20to%20capture%20them%20so%20far%2C%20said%20a%20source%20involved%20with%20the%20Project%20Cheetah.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAnother%20source%20said%20that%20the%20teams%20tried%20darting%20the%20animals%20%E2%80%9Ca%20few%20times%2C%20but%20failed%E2%80%9D%2C%20possibly%20because%20the%20animals%20are%20%E2%80%9Cvery%20shy%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20sources%20did%20not%20want%20to%20be%20named%20as%20the%20Madhya%20Pradesh%20state%20government%20had%20announced%20a%20gag%20order%20on%20officials%20associated%20with%20the%20project%20last%20week%20which%20prevents%20them%20from%20officially%20talking%20to%20the%20media%20about%20the%20latest%20developments%20in%20the%20programme.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThere%20were%20%E2%80%9Cproblems%E2%80%9D%20with%20Nirva%E2%80%99s%20radio%20collar%2C%20but%20monitoring%20teams%20are%20observing%20the%20animal%20closely%2C%20one%20of%20the%20sources%20said.%20The%20teams%20sighted%20her%20directly%20and%20were%20also%20able%20to%20see%20her%20pugmarks%20and%20other%20indirect%20signs%20%E2%80%93%20so%20there%20is%20no%20need%20to%20%E2%80%9Cworry%E2%80%9D%20about%20the%20animal%2C%20the%20source%20added.%20Plans%20are%20still%20on%20to%20capture%20the%20two%20animals%2C%20the%20source%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1690554927000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fupl