Students%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2021%2F09%2F19131851%2FStephens-pti.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENew%20Delhi%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20St%20Stephen%E2%80%99s%20and%20Jesus%20and%20Mary%20colleges%20will%20be%20allowed%20to%20give%2015%25%20weightage%20to%20interviews%20for%20admissions%20under%20the%20Christian%20minority%20quota%20for%20the%202023-24%20academic%20year%2C%20the%20Delhi%20high%20court%20ruled%20in%20a%20recent%20order.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESt%20Stephen%E2%80%99s%20had%20challenged%20the%20decision%20of%20the%20Executive%20Council%20of%20the%20Delhi%20University%20(DU)%20and%20a%20University%20Grants%20Commission%20(UGC)%20notification%20issued%20on%20December%2030%2C%202022%20that%20insisted%20that%20all%20colleges%20should%20give%20100%25%20weightage%20for%20Common%20University%20Entrance%20Test%20(CUET)%20scores%2C%20even%20for%20minority%20quota%20admissions.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.barandbench.com%2Fnews%2Flitigation%2Fdelhi-high-court-st-stephens-college-15-weightage-interviews-admission-christian-students%5C%22%3EAccording%20to%20%3Cem%3EBar%20and%20Bench%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20the%20division%20Bench%20of%20Chief%20Justice%20Satish%20Chandra%20Sharma%20and%20Justice%20Subramonium%20Prasad%20passed%20an%20interim%20order%20on%20July%2021%20allowing%20the%20college%20to%20give%20weightage%20to%20interview%20of%20Christian%20quota%20candidates.%20However%2C%20the%20court%20reiterated%20it%20will%20have%20to%20give%20100%25%20weightage%20to%20CUET%20scores%20for%20admissions%20under%20the%20unreserved%20category.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Delhi%20high%20court%20had%20already%20passed%20an%20order%20in%20September%202022%20allowing%20the%20college%20to%C2%A0give%20weightage%20to%20interviews%20for%20admission%20of%20reserved%20category%20students.%20The%20order%20was%20appealled%20before%20the%20Supreme%20Court%2C%20where%20the%20matter%20is%20pending%20a%20decision.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAfter%20considering%20the%20case%2C%20the%20Bench%20noted%20that%20in%20its%20decision%20of%20September%202022%2C%20it%20had%20recognised%20that%20it%20is%20for%20the%20minority%20institutions%20to%20decide%20what%20would%20be%20best%20for%20the%20minority%20community.%20For%20that%20purpose%2C%20conducting%20an%20interview%20cannot%20be%20said%20to%20be%20contrary%20to%20the%20interest%20of%20the%20minority%20institution%2C%20the%20court%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20%3Cem%3EBar%20and%20Bench%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20the%20HC%20said%20in%20its%20recent%20order%20that%20%E2%80%9Callowing%20the%20petitioner%20college%20to%20admit%20students%20from%20the%20minority%20community%20by%20giving%2085%25%20weightage%20to%20their%20CUET%20scores%20and%2015%25%20weightage%20to%20their%20interview%2C%20would%20be%20best%20for%20furthering%20their%20interest%E2%80%9D.%20The%20colleges%20will%20be%20allowed%20to%20do%20so%20for%20the%202023-24%20academic%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20bench%20said%20that%20there%20was%20%E2%80%9Ca%20complete%20lack%20of%20reasoning%20as%20to%20why%20the%20%5Drevious%5D%20judgment%20of%20this%20court%20has%20been%20given%20a%20go-by%20by%20the%20respondents%20(DU%20and%20UGC)%20and%20indicates%20non-application%20of%20mind%20on%20their%20part%E2%80%9D%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fcity%2Fdelhi%2Fst-stephens-jesus-and-mary-colleges-can-hold-interviews-for-christian-candidates-seeking-admission%2Farticleshow%2F102184554.cms%3Ffrom%3Dmdr%5C%22%3Eaccording%20to%20the%20%3Cem%3ETimes%20of%20India%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1690528527000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2021%2F09%2F19131851%2FStephens-pti.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fdelhi-hc-st-stephens-15-weightage-interviews-christian-students%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22St%20Stephen's%20had%20challenged%20the%2