Latika%20(previously%20Latika%20Roy%20Foundation%2C%20or%20LRF)%2C%20an%20organisation%20that%20has%2C%20since%201994%2C%20worked%20with%20thousands%20of%20children%20and%20adults%20with%20intellectual%20and%20physical%20disabilities%20to%20help%20them%20mainstream%20in%20society.%20Among%20their%20key%20projects%20is%20to%20work%20with%20disabled%20children%20in%20their%20early%20years%2C%20to%20%E2%80%9Ccatch%20them%20young%E2%80%9D%2C%20as%20one%20of%20their%20programmes%20says.%20This%20inclusion%20centres%20around%20their%20education%2C%20but%20also%20looks%20to%20integrate%20them%20into%20the%20mainstream%20as%20a%20whole%20and%20for%20the%20long%20term.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CWhen%20Maria%20Montessori%20began%20her%20work%2C%20it%20was%20for%20disabled%20children.%20But%20parents%20soon%20realised%20that%20this%20could%20work%20for%20other%20children%20too.%20That%E2%80%99s%20what%20we%E2%80%99re%20always%20telling%20people%2C%20that%20when%20you%20target%20the%20most%20vulnerable%20child%20in%20the%20room%2C%20your%20whole%20classroom%20will%20benefit%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20tells%20%3Cstrong%3EThe%20Better%20India%3C%2Fstrong%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3E%E2%80%98Everybody%20is%20welcome%E2%80%99%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELatika%E2%80%99s%20work%20with%20disabled%20children%20began%20when%20Jo%20and%20her%20husband%20Ravi%20adopted%20Moy%20Moy%2C%20who%20also%20lived%20with%20a%20disability.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CWe%20started%20as%20just%20an%20inclusive%20play%20centre%20where%20children%20of%20all%20kinds%20could%20come%20after%20school%20and%20engage%20in%20fun%20activities.%20The%20only%20rules%20were%20that%20you%20play%20fair%20and%20welcome%20everybody%2C%E2%80%9D%20Jo%20tells%20%3Cstrong%3EThe%20Better%20India%3C%2Fstrong%3E.%20%E2%80%9CWe%20saw%20lots%20of%20kids%20with%20disabilities%20coming%20in%20naturally%3B%20it%20wasn%E2%80%99t%20an%20active%20effort%20on%20our%20part%2C%20but%20they%20came%20because%20of%20the%20inclusive%20environment%20we%E2%80%99d%20built.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cblockquote%20data-instgrm-captioned%20data-instgrm-version%3D%5C%2214%5C%22%20data-instgrm-permalink%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.instagram.com%2Fp%2FClDz_IEOdMY%2F%3Futm_source%3Dig_embed%26amp%3Butm_campaign%3Dloading%5C%22%3E%3Cdiv%3E%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.instagram.com%2Fp%2FClDz_IEOdMY%2F%3Futm_source%3Dig_embed%26utm_campaign%3Dloading%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%20%3Cdiv%3E%20%3Cdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Cdiv%3E%20%3Cdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Cdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Cdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3E%20%3Cdiv%3EView%20this%20post%20on%20Instagram%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Cdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3E%20%3Cdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Cdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Cdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3E%20%3Cdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Cdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3E%20%3Cdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Cdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Cdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Cdiv%3E%20%3Cdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Cdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.instagram.com%2Fp%2FClDz_IEOdMY%2F%3Futm_source%3Dig_embed%26utm_campaign%3Dloading%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EA%20post%20shared%20by%20Latika%20Roy%20Foundation%20(%40latikaroyfoundation)%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3C%2Fblockquote%3E%20%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhat%20they%20learnt%20later%2C%20she%20says%2C%20was%20that%20these%20children%20with%20disabilities%20couldn%E2%80%99t%20otherwise%20engage%20in%20regular%20childhood%20activities%20like%20going%20to%20the%20park%20and%20that%20they%20often%20had%20no%20friends.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThen%20it%20turned%20out%20that%20my%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thebetterindia.com%2F291203%2Fdaughter-down-syndrome-made-amarjit-singh-anand-start-chaanan-home-for-disabled-kids-punjab%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eown%20daughter%20was%20disabled%3C%2Fa%3E.%20We%20hadn%E2%80%99t%20looked%20at%20it%20that%20way%20until%20she%20had%20to%20go%20to%20school.%20Then%20her%20disabilities%20really%20became%20apparent.%20For%20us%2C%20she%20was%20just%20Moy%20Moy%2C%20this%20great%2C%20funny%2C%20little%20child.%20But%20when%20she%20started%20going%20to%20school%2C%20it%20was%20as%20if%20they%20put%20a%20spotlight%20on%20her%20difficulties.%20That%E2%80%99s%20when%20we%20realised%20this%20school%20system%20wasn%E2%80%99t%20right%20for%20Moy%20Moy.%20Everything%20at%20the%20Foundation%20has%20evolved%20from%20that.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIndia%20has%20put%20in%20place%20many%20provisions%20in%20the%20form%20of%20laws%20and%20policies%20for%20people%20with%20disabilities%2C%20but%20the%20implementation%20remains%20questionable.%20%3Cem%3EOutlook%20India%20%3C%2Fem%3Enoted%20of%20all%20the%20children%20with%20disabilities%20in%20India%2C%20three-fourths%20of%20those%20aged%20aged%20five%20don%E2%80%99t%20attend%20any%20educational%20institution.%20About%2012%25%20drop%20out%2C%20and%2027%25%20have%20never%20attended%20any%20educational%20institute.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMeanwhile%2C%20a%20UNICEF%20report%20notes%2C%20%E2%80%9CThe%20early%20years%20(0%20to%208%20years)%20are%20the%20most%20extraordinary%20period%20of%20growth%20and%20development%20in%20a%20child%E2%80%99s%20lifetime.%20The%20foundations%20of%20all%20learning%20are%20laid%20during%20these%20years.%20Getting%20the%20foundations%20right%20carries%20huge%20future%20benefits%3A%20better%20learning%20in%20school%20and%20higher%20educational%20attainment%2C%20which%20results%20in%20major%20social%20and%20economic%20gains%20for%20society.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-image%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20820px)%20100vw%2C%20820px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2Finclusive-education-1690291697.jpg%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22820%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22inclusive%20education%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2Finclusive-education-1690291697.jpg%20820w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2Finclusive-education-1690291697-300x169.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2Finclusive-education-1690291697-500x282.jpg%20500w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2Finclusive-education-1690291697-768x433.jpg%20768w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2Finclusive-education-1690291697-150x85.jpg%20150w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-325144%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22462%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%20class%3D%5C%22wp-element-caption%5C%22%3EUNICEF%20reports%20that%20the%20early%20years%20are%20the%20most%20extraordinary%20period%20of%20growth%20and%20development%20in%20a%20child%E2%80%99s%20lifetime%3B%20Photo%3A%20Representational%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%202020%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thebetterindia.com%2F234151%2Fnew-education-policy-2020-pdf-hrd-ministry-play-school-classes-vocational-coding-bagless-information-vid01%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ENational%20Education%20Policy%3C%2Fa%3E%20has%20laid%20great%20emphasis%20on%20inclusion%20in%20education%20that%20takes%20into%20consideration%20local%20contexts%20and%20diversity.%20The%20framework%20asserts%20that%20quality%20in%20the%20early%20childhood%20care%20ecosystem%20(ECCE)%20is%20the%20highest%20priority%2C%20as%20is%20the%20inclusion%20and%20equal%20participation%20of%20children%20with%20disabilities%20and%20those%20from%20economically%20disadvantaged%20groups.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESo%20how%20do%20we%20extend%20the%20same%20future%20benefits%20to%20children%20with%20disabilities%2C%20who%20are%20disproportionately%20affected%20by%20an%20already%20fractured%20educational%20system%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAmong%20the%20first%20programmes%20that%20the%20Foundation%20started%20was%20Karuna%20Vihar%2C%20an%20early%20childhood%20intervention%20centre%20that%20encourages%20the%20overall%20development%20of%20children%20between%20the%20ages%20of%200%20and%206%20by%20building%20on%20their%20strengths.%20Parents%20or%20guardians%20work%20closely%20with%20special%20educators%20and%20therapists%20so%20they%20can%20carry%20out%20the%20activities%20practised%20during%20lessons%20at%20home.%20They%20are%20also%20given%20counselling%20services%20and%20support%20group%20interventions.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EKaruna%20Vihar%20also%20focuses%20on%20%E2%80%98play%E2%80%99%20including%20theatre%20and%20creative%20interventions%20like%20exercises%20to%20help%20develop%20a%20child%E2%80%99s%20functional%20skills.%20They%20also%20involve%20play%20in%20developing%20individualised%20education%20plans%20for%20each%20child%20to%20learn%20speech%20and%20language%20skills%20and%20alternative%20communication%20systems%2C%20as%20well%20as%20encourage%20sensory%20stimulation%20and%20behaviour%20management.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3ECrucial%20aspects%20of%20a%20person%E2%80%99s%20life%C2%A0%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERupa%20Bishnoi%2C%20director%20of%20diversity%20and%20inclusion%20at%20Latika%2C%20tells%20%3Cstrong%3EThe%20Better%20India%3C%2Fstrong%3E%2C%20%E2%80%9CWhen%20we%20talk%20about%20%E2%80%98inclusive%20education%E2%80%99%2C%20we%20also%20mean%20their%20inclusion%20in%20society.%20We%20have%20two%20catchwords%20%E2%80%94%20%E2%80%98participation%E2%80%99%20and%20%E2%80%98opportunity%E2%80%99.%20I%20specifically%20work%20for%20the%20mainstreaming%20of%20our%20children%20with%20the%20kids%2C%20the%20parents%2C%20and%20the%20schools.%20Preparing%20the%20schools%20has%20become%20the%20main%20focus%20area%20for%20the%20inclusion%20team.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20is%20commonplace%20in%20India%20for%20school%20managements%20to%20deny%20opportunities%20to%20children%20with%20disabilities%20%E2%80%94%20sometimes%20due%20to%20a%20lack%20of%20understanding%2C%20and%20sometimes%20due%20to%20an%20unwillingness%20to%20%E2%80%9Ctake%20responsibility%E2%80%9D.%20Children%20may%20also%20face%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thebetterindia.com%2F302809%2Fanoushka-jolly-shark-tank-started-kavach-an-app-for-bullying%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ebullying%20and%20discrimination%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20these%20institutions%2C%20often%20with%20limited%20intervention%20by%20school%20authorities.%20Then%20there%20is%20a%20lack%20of%20accessible%20and%20safe%20infrastructure%2C%20and%20special%20educators.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CWe%20work%20on%20a%20process%20where%20we%20contact%20schools%2C%20hold%20workshops%20with%20them%2C%20make%20them%20aware%20of%20different%20disabilities%2C%20establish%20relationships%E2%80%A6then%20we%20try%20to%20mainstream%20our%20children.%20For%20at%20least%20a%20year%20of%20support%2C%20we%20provide%20teachers%20with%20strategies%2C%20and%20work%20preventing%20the%20bullying%20of%20even%20parents%E2%80%A6This%20way%20we%E2%80%99ve%20managed%20to%20mainstream%20nine%20children%20in%20the%20last%20two%20years.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cblockquote%20data-instgrm-captioned%20data-instgrm-version%3D%5C%2214%5C%22%20data-instgrm-permalink%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.instagram.com%2Fp%2FCuXG-KtOEuJ%2F%3Futm_source%3Dig_embed%26amp%3Butm_campaign%3Dloading%5C%22%3E%3Cdiv%3E%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.instagram.com%2Fp%2FCuXG-KtOEuJ%2F%3Futm_source%3Dig_embed%26utm_campaign%3Dloading%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%20%3Cdiv%3E%20%3Cdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Cdiv%3E%20%3Cdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Cdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Cdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3E%20%3Cdiv%3EView%20this%20post%20on%20Inst